    <fr:title text="Matrix Equality">Matrix Equality</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}=[a_{i,j}]]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {B}=[b_{i,j}]]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrices. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {B}]]></fr:tex> are <html:dfn>Equal</html:dfn> if they have identical components in identical positions, i.e., if for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i=1,…,m]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j=1,…,n]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{i,j}=b_{i,j}]]></fr:tex>. We indicate the matrices are equal by writing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}=\mathbf {B}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
    <html:p>More formally: let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {B}]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\times  q]]></fr:tex> matrix, if:
<html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m = p]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n = q]]></fr:tex> and</html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathbf {A})_{ij}=(\mathbf {B})_{ij}]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i=1,…,m]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j=1,…,n]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A} = \mathbf {B}.]]></fr:tex></html:p>
    <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {B}]]></fr:tex> are not equal, then we write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}\neq \mathbf {B}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
