                <fr:route>/matrix-0003/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="zero matrix">zero matrix</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>For any positive integers <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, we have the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Zero Matrix</html:dfn> to be the matrix whose components are all zero. We denote this by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {0}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex> because it will play the analogous counterpart that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> plays.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
