                <fr:display-uri>matrix-0004</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/matrix-0004/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="identity matrix">identity matrix</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>For any positive integer <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, we have the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  n]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Identity Matrix</html:dfn> to be
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {I}_{n} = (\delta _{i,j}) = \begin {cases}1 &\hbox {if }i=j,\\
    0 &\hbox {if }i\neq  j
  \end {cases}]]></fr:tex>
where the components <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _{i,j}]]></fr:tex> are referred to as the <html:dfn>Kronecker Delta</html:dfn>.</html:p>
                <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> is clear from context, we may suppress the subscript and write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {I}]]></fr:tex> instead of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {I}_{n}]]></fr:tex>. Some authors write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {1}]]></fr:tex> for the identity matrix, because (as we will see) it is analogous to the number <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
