                <fr:display-uri>matrix-0005</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/matrix-0005/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="vectors">vectors</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:dfn>Column Vector</html:dfn> refers to an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times 1]]></fr:tex> matrix.</html:p>
                <html:p>A <html:dfn>Row Vector</html:dfn> refers to a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1\times  m]]></fr:tex> matrix.</html:p>
                <html:p>A <html:dfn>Vector</html:dfn> may refer to either row vectors or column vectors; in these notes on elementary linear algebra, we will reserve the word "vector" specifically for "column vector".</html:p>
                <html:p>Also note: it is common convention to use superscript indices for column vectors, and subscript indices for row vectors. This allows for the Einstein summation convention to do some stuff automatically for us.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
