                <fr:uri>http://localhost:8000/matrix-0007/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>matrix-0007</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/matrix-0007/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="scalar matrix">scalar matrix</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A diagonal matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}=(a_{i,j})]]></fr:tex> for which <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{i,i}=c]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> is called a <html:dfn>Scalar Matrix</html:dfn>.</html:p>
                <html:p>The word "scalar" intuitively means "number". We <fr:link href="/ela-0009/" title="enter the matrix" uri="http://localhost:8000/ela-0009/" display-uri="ela-0009" type="local">motivated</fr:link> matrices by trying to generalize numbers. Scalar matrices are "the most number-like" among matrices.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
