                <fr:title text="Upper-triangular matrix">Upper-triangular matrix</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>We call an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}=(a_{i,j})]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Upper Triangular</html:dfn> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{i,j}=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i>j]]></fr:tex>, e.g., when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m=n]]></fr:tex> it looks like: <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A} = \begin {bmatrix}
    a_{1,1} & a_{1,2} & a_{1,3} & … & a_{1,n}\\
    0      & a_{2,2} & a_{2,3} & … & a_{2,n}\\
    0      & 0       & a_{3,3} & … & a_{3,n}\\
    \vdots  & \vdots  & \vdots  & \ddots  & \vdots \\
    0      & 0      & 0      & …  & a_{n,n}
  \end {bmatrix}]]></fr:tex></html:p>
                <html:p>Furthermore, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{i,i}=0]]></fr:tex>, then we call <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Strictly Upper Triangular</html:dfn>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
