            <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For any matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}-\mathbf {A}=\mathbf {0}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>5</fr:month><fr:day>26</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
<html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}=(a_{ij})]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}-\mathbf {A}=(a_{ij}-a_{ij})=(0)]]></fr:tex>. Since every entry is zero, it must be equal to the <fr:link href="/matrix-0003/" title="zero matrix" uri="http://localhost:8000/matrix-0003/" display-uri="matrix-0003" type="local">zero matrix</fr:link> by definition of <fr:link href="/matrix-0009/" title="Matrix Equality" uri="http://localhost:8000/matrix-0009/" display-uri="matrix-0009" type="local">Matrix Equality</fr:link>. Hence the result.</html:p>
<html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
